Tomato Goat Cheese Risotto
  --Cook's Country
  
4 c chicken broth, divided
1 c arborio rice
5 tbsp unsalted butter, divided
1/2 tsp table salt
1/2 tsp pepper
1 onion, chopped fine
3 plum tomato, cored and chopped
2 garlic cloves, minced
1/2 c dry white wine
2 oz goat cheese, crumbled (1/2 c)

Microwave 3 c broth, rice, and 2 tbsp butter in large covered bowl until most of liquid is absorbed, 12-16 min. Melt 2 tbsp butter in skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and salt and cook until softened, ~3 min. Stir in tomatoes and garlic and cook until fragrant, ~1 min. Stir in wine and simmer until reduced by half, ~2 min. Add rice and remaining 1 c broth. Bring to simmer and cook, stirring constantly, until rice is al dente, 4-6 min. Off heat, stir in goat cheese and remaining 1 tbsp butter. 
